# Cloudflare Pages routing for eliza-cloud frontend (Vite SPA)
# Format docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Order matters: top-down, first match wins.
#
# /api/* and /steward/* are handled by Pages Functions, which proxy server-side
# to the Workers API (true same-origin, no CORS preflight). Pages Functions take
# precedence over _redirects, so adding rewrite rules here would be misleading
# dead config.
# The free-tier 200-rewrite to an external origin does not actually proxy.

# Docs have moved to the unified Mintlify site at docs.elizaos.ai/cloud.
# The /docs/api/* rule must precede /docs/* so API paths don't get mangled
# by the catch-all (first-match-wins).
/docs/api             https://docs.elizaos.ai/cloud/api          301
/docs/api/*           https://docs.elizaos.ai/cloud/api/:splat   301
/docs                 https://docs.elizaos.ai/cloud              301
/docs/*               https://docs.elizaos.ai/cloud/:splat       301

# SPA fallback — every other path falls through to index.html so React
# Router can resolve client-side routes.
/*  /index.html  200
